{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-post-template-js","path":"/blog/2024-08-07-how-to-add-mixed-background-color-in-react-js/","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"excerpt":"Hi Friends üëã, Welcome To aHoisting! To add mixed background color in react js, you can set  in . It will add mixed background color in react js. Today, I am‚Ä¶","html":"<p>Hi Friends üëã,</p>\n<p>Welcome To aHoisting!</p>\n<p>To add mixed background color in react js, you can set <code class=\"language-text\">background: linear-gradient(to right, #7520cf, #e3c7b1);</code> in <code class=\"language-text\">mixed-background</code>. It will add mixed background color in react js.</p>\n<p>Today, I am going to show you, how to add mixed background color in react js.</p>\n<p>Table of contents</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Install and create a new React app.</li>\n<li>Import react component.</li>\n<li>Create a Component.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Let‚Äôs start with the first step.</p>\n<h2>Step 1: Install and create a new React app.</h2>\n<p>First you have to install the React project. You should use <code class=\"language-text\">create-react-app</code> command to create a new React project.</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"js\"><pre class=\"language-js\"><code class=\"language-js\">npx create<span class=\"token operator\">-</span>react<span class=\"token operator\">-</span>app my<span class=\"token operator\">-</span>app\ncd my<span class=\"token operator\">-</span>app\nnpm start</code></pre></div>\n<h2>Step 2: Import react component.</h2>\n<p>After installing, you have to import your React component.</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"js\"><pre class=\"language-js\"><code class=\"language-js\"><span class=\"token keyword\">import</span> React <span class=\"token keyword\">from</span> <span class=\"token string\">'react'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token keyword\">import</span> <span class=\"token string\">'./App.css'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span></code></pre></div>\n<h2>Step 3: Create a Component.</h2>\n<p>You can use <code class=\"language-text\">className=\"mixed-background\"</code> to add mixed background color in react js.</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"js\"><pre class=\"language-js\"><code class=\"language-js\"><span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span>div className<span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token string\">\"mixed-background\"</span><span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n  <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span>h1<span class=\"token operator\">></span>Mixed Background Color<span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span><span class=\"token operator\">/</span>h1<span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n<span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span><span class=\"token operator\">/</span>div<span class=\"token operator\">></span></code></pre></div>\n<h2>Add mixed background color example.</h2>\n<p>The below code is an example of a React. You have to import <code class=\"language-text\">./App.css</code> and set <code class=\"language-text\">background: linear-gradient(to right, #7520cf, #e3c7b1);</code> in <code class=\"language-text\">mixed-background</code> to add mixed background color in react js.</p>\n<p><code class=\"language-text\">App.js</code></p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"js\"><pre class=\"language-js\"><code class=\"language-js\">\n<span class=\"token keyword\">import</span> React <span class=\"token keyword\">from</span> <span class=\"token string\">'react'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token keyword\">import</span> <span class=\"token string\">'./App.css'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n\n<span class=\"token keyword\">const</span> <span class=\"token function-variable function\">App</span> <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token operator\">=></span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n  <span class=\"token keyword\">return</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>\n    <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span>div className<span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token string\">\"mixed-background\"</span><span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n      <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span>h1<span class=\"token operator\">></span>Mixed Background Color<span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span><span class=\"token operator\">/</span>h1<span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n    <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span><span class=\"token operator\">/</span>div<span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n  <span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n\n<span class=\"token keyword\">export</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">default</span> App<span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span></code></pre></div>\n<p><code class=\"language-text\">App.css</code></p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"css\"><pre class=\"language-css\"><code class=\"language-css\"><span class=\"token comment\">/* App.css */</span>\n<span class=\"token selector\">.mixed-background</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n  <span class=\"token property\">background</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> <span class=\"token function\">linear-gradient</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>to right<span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> #7520cf<span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> #e3c7b1<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span> \n  <span class=\"token property\">height</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> 100vh<span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span> \n  <span class=\"token property\">display</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> flex<span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n  <span class=\"token property\">align-items</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> center<span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n  <span class=\"token property\">justify-content</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> center<span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span></code></pre></div>\n<p>In the above code example, I have used the <code class=\"language-text\">background: linear-gradient(to right, #7520cf, #e3c7b1);</code> to add mixed background color in react js.</p>\n<p>Check the output of the above code.</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 630px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/6804ba92bcb5b8e310e456f40cfefc69/89344/mixed-background-color.webp\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 51.26582278481012%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/webp;base64,UklGRmQAAABXRUJQVlA4IFgAAAAwBACdASoUAAoAPtFWo0uoJKMhsAgBABoJZgCdMoR4GCIRAReIAFScOEAA/nEqY+EBzBWjYTl/UbfKWW7wKA3WjZ9gMoxQHpM1PtNm3KlW5sgh1kcxf2AA'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"React, add, mixed, background, color\"\n        title=\"React, add, mixed, background, color\"\n        src=\"/static/6804ba92bcb5b8e310e456f40cfefc69/8aab1/mixed-background-color.webp\"\n        srcset=\"/static/6804ba92bcb5b8e310e456f40cfefc69/81b7c/mixed-background-color.webp 158w,\n/static/6804ba92bcb5b8e310e456f40cfefc69/6ea66/mixed-background-color.webp 315w,\n/static/6804ba92bcb5b8e310e456f40cfefc69/8aab1/mixed-background-color.webp 630w,\n/static/6804ba92bcb5b8e310e456f40cfefc69/a70f5/mixed-background-color.webp 945w,\n/static/6804ba92bcb5b8e310